Overview
	trainControl is a program that implement a simple POSIX Threads train
	time control.

Compiling
	Do you need the build-essential, pthreads and SDL libs packages instaled
	in your system to compile this program. In a debian-based linux you can
	install by the simple execution of this command:
	
	sudo apt-get install build-essential
	
	If you obtain this software in a tarball gunzip archive, just do:
	
	tar -xzf train-control0.1-0.tar.gz
	
	To compile this software, goto main directory and do:
	
	make
	
Basics
	To run this program, execute this command in the main directory:
	
	./bin/trainControl
	
	Follow the screen instruction.

